com.xjeffrose.xio.pipeline

Class SmartHttpPipeline

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xjeffrose.xio.pipeline.XioBasePipeline

        • com.xjeffrose.xio.pipeline.SmartHttpPipeline
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    XioPipelineFragment

    public class SmartHttpPipeline
extends XioServerPipeline
    SmartHttpPipeline does http well. If configured with a certificate pair (which it should be by default), it will: - accept incoming TLS and negotiate the application protocol - supporting http/2 requests if the client can - supporting http/1 requests as a fallback - try to upgrade plain text requests with http response code 426 - http/1.1 over cleartext if configured to do so (not the default)
